comparative_cover_evaluation.user_prompt_template:
Compare these two cover designs for: {title} by {author}

Genre: {genre}
Target Audience: {target_audience}

**Design A:**
[Description: {design_a_description}]

**Design B:**
[Description: {design_b_description}]

Evaluation Criteria:
{criteria_list}

Provide:
1. Head-to-head comparison on each criterion
2. Overall winner and detailed reasoning
3. What each design does well
4. How the losing design could be improved
5. Market appeal analysis

Return as JSON:
{{
  "comparison": {{
    "winner": "A" or "B",
    "confidence": 0.0-1.0,
    "rationale": "Detailed explanation",
    "criterion_comparison": {{
      "criterion_name": {{"a_score": 0-10, "b_score": 0-10, "analysis": "Why"}}
    }},
    "design_a_strengths": ["Strength 1", "Strength 2"],
    "design_b_strengths": ["Strength 1", "Strength 2"],
    "loser_improvement_path": "Specific revision suggestions",
    "thumbnail_test": {{"winner": "A"|"B", "notes": "Which works better small"}},
    "shelf_appeal": {{"winner": "A"|"B", "notes": "Which stands out more"}},
    "target_audience_appeal": "Which resonates more with {target_audience}"
  }}
}}

design_prompt_generation.user_prompt_template:
Create a detailed image generation prompt for a book cover:

Title: {title}
Subtitle: {subtitle}
Author: {author}
Genre: {genre}
Target Audience: {target_audience}
Book Summary: {summary}
Key Themes: {themes}
Author Vision: {author_vision}

Competitive Covers (describe visual elements):
{comp_covers}

Generate a prompt that:
1. Captures genre conventions
2. Creates visual impact
3. Reflects key themes
4. Differentiates from competition
5. Appeals to target audience
6. Is technically feasible

Return as JSON:
{{
  "prompts": {{
    "midjourney": "Detailed MJ prompt with parameters",
    "dalle3": "DALL-E 3 optimized prompt",
    "stable_diffusion": "SD prompt with parameters"
  }},
  "rationale": "Why these visual choices",
  "style_notes": "Artistic style and mood",
  "color_palette": "Suggested colors and why",
  "typography_notes": "Font style recommendations"
}}
